.TH "omap3_enter_idle_bm" 9 "omap3_enter_idle_bm" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
omap3_enter_idle_bm \- Checks for any bus activity
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" omap3_enter_idle_bm
.BI "(struct cpuidle_device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct cpuidle_driver *drv "  ","
.BI "int index "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
cpuidle device
.IP "drv" 12
cpuidle driver
.IP "index" 12
array index of target state to be programmed
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function checks for any pending activity and then programs
the device to the specified or a safer state.
